section.section:
Nothing in this section shall be construed to prohibit a transportation provider from:
Contracting with nonprofit organizations, public transportation providers, or private carriers for the provision of transportation service to low-income workers;
Modifying or expanding an existing local transportation system;
Developing a new transportation system with the use or assistance of subsidized volunteers; or
Allowing individuals other than low-income workers to use the transportation services provided by the job access project to the extent excess capacity is available.
